# Overview
***

Website for the submission and hosting of code for [CPE 470: Autonomous Mobile Robots](http://www.cse.unr.edu/~monica/Courses/CPE470-670/index.html) with [Monica Nicolescu](http://www.cse.unr.edu/~monica/). We are using [BricxCC](http://bricxcc.sourceforge.net/) to design, build, and run the programs for the NXT Mindstorm Lego Kit.

# Lab 2
***
###[Github: Lab 2](https://github.com/jakecsells/AutoMobileRobots/tree/master/Lab02)
The entire lab can be downloaded from our gibhub page or downloaded from this website. The solution to lab 2 is within the folder "Lab02".

We successfully completed lab 2 by finishing each mini-program for the lab.

The most complex of the programs written is the multi-tasking program. This program required a mutex to control which function has control of the robot at a certain time.

###Mutex Example:
```c++
mutex control;
...
task check_sensors()
{
  while (true)
  {
    Acquire(control);
    
    // If left sensor pressed
...
    Release(control);
  }
}
...
// Move forward at 50% power
task move_forward()
{
  while (true)
  {
    Acquire(control);
    OnFwd(OUT_AC, 50);
    Release(control);
  }
}
```

# Lab 1
***
For lab one, we built the generic NXT Mindstorm Lego Robot with the kit.

![Lego NXT Robot](https://raw.github.com/jakecsells/AutoMobileRobots/master/Lab01/mindstorm_nxt_design.jpg)

Pictured is not a picture of our robot, but a picture of the design that we used.
